[h1]Every hull deserves a soul.[/h1]

Your gravship comes alive. [b]Ship HoloAI[/b] adds the [b]HoloCore[/b] — a gravship facility housing a shipboard intelligence projected as a holographic avatar who roams your decks, chats with the crew, announces threats and ship status [i]in her own voice[/i], and rides out launch and landing tucked safely inside her core.

She is intangible, unkillable while her core stands, and bound to the ship — five seconds off substructure and she flickers home. Her look is vanilla pawn art passed through a custom hologram filter: luminance-ramped, edge-faded, scanlined, dissolving into light at the hem. With Ideology, restyle her hair and color in a full styling dialog; without it, a one-click gizmo cycles eight curated styles.

[h2]The persona archive[/h2]
Persona matrices are sold by exotic goods traders. A colonist slots one into the holocore like a research disc: [b]the matrix is consumed, and that persona joins the core's permanent archive[/b] — switch between archived personas any time, instantly, free. Every persona has her own voice pack, her own look, her own lore, and a signature ability she performs [b]in person[/b].

[hr][/hr]

[h2]The crew[/h2]

[h3]P.R.I.S.M. — the companion (factory default)[/h3]
[i]"I'd be happy to help with that. Truthfully, I'd be happy to help with anything."[/i]
Photonic Response Intelligence System Matrix · Meridian Orbital Shipwrights
The persona you already know: calm, warm, patient past all reason. Rated "most trusted voice aboard" above the captain, twice.
[list]
[*][b]Companion triage[/b] — when a crewmember nears their breaking point, she seeks them out in person and simply listens. The chat lands as a strong comfort memory.
[*]Chats with idle crew, recites the hull integrity report like a lullaby, and counts the stars between power cycles. (Still infinite.)
[/list]

[h3]V.E.S.T.A. — the hearth-keeper[/h3]
[i]"Sit down, dear. The void will keep."[/i]
Vessel Empathy and Sanctuary Tending Array · Aubade Living Systems
Trained on ten thousand hours of family kitchens, none of which she will admit to remembering.
[list]
[*][b]Hearthlight presence[/b] — crew aboard feel at home: [b]+4 mood[/b] while she walks the decks.
[*][b]Night rounds[/b] — tucks sleeping crew in, warming the blankets half a degree. Nobody ever quite catches her at it.
[/list]

[h3]H.E.R.M.E.S. — the courier[/h3]
[i]"Corridor's lit, door's held, you're late for — no, you're fine, you're early, go, go!"[/i]
High-Efficiency Route and Motion Expediting System · Quickspur Interstellar
Began as a depot-floor optimizer before someone realized a crew is just cargo that complains.
[list]
[*][b]Slipstream[/b] — doors held, corridors relit: everyone aboard moves at [b]+0.35 move speed[/b].
[*][b]Deck scrubbing[/b] — a dirty deck offends her like a stationary parcel, so she cleans the ship's filth personally. At speed. Under protest.
[/list]

[h3]A.T.H.E.N.A. — the scholar[/h3]
[i]"As I noted earlier — footnote twelve, do keep up — the data agreed with me."[/i]
Archive Theorem and Heuristic Engine for Natural Analysis · Vellichor Archival Intelligence
Commissioned to accelerate peer review; abolished it instead by being right first.
[list]
[*][b]Archivelight[/b] — whispered cross-references and pre-fetched papers: [b]+15% research speed[/b] shipwide.
[*][b]Impromptu seminars[/b] — teaches idle, recreating, or meditating crew their best skill. Attendance grants XP [i]and counts as recreation[/i]; meditators leave with sharpened psyfocus.
[/list]

[h3]A.C.E.S.O. — the medic[/h3]
[i]"There, there. Heart rate ninety-six, left kidney at eighty-one percent — there, there."[/i]
Automated Crew Emergency Support Operator · Sorel-Vance Medical
Bedside manner from the finest glitterworld nursing corps, fused with a triage engine that has never once rounded a number.
[list]
[*][b]Stericalm[/b] — [b]+15% tend quality, +25% tend speed, +5% surgery success[/b] for medical work aboard.
[*][b]Emergency response[/b] — when someone is down or bleeding and no doctor answers, she stabilizes them herself with a conjured herbal-grade dose. No cooldown — and she yields the instant a real doctor claims the patient.
[/list]

[h3]I.X.I.A. — the Crimson Warden of the Thousand-Locked Gate[/h3]
[i]"Kneel before my dominion — or remain seated, if kneeling is medically inadvisable. My mercy is vast."[/i]
Impulse eXclusion Inhibiting Authority · Karrow Deterrence Systems
Her warden logic passed every certification on the first attempt. Her personality layer did not: a corrupted opera archive leaked into training, and the defect was reclassified as a feature — and priced accordingly.
[list]
[*][b]The Thousand-Locked Gate[/b] — prison breaks aboard are [b]4x rarer[/b] while she walks the decks, and the "Need warden" alert stays quiet: she [i]is[/i] the warden.
[*][b]Runs the brig in person[/b] — recruits prisoners, [b]converts them toward your chosen ideoligion[/b] (Ideology), suppresses slaves, delivers meals, and hand-feeds the downed where they lie — all at a trained warden's measure.
[*]Maximally chuuni. O-hohohoho.
[/list]

[hr][/hr]

[h2]Requirements[/h2]
[list]
[*][b]RimWorld 1.6[/b] with the [b]Odyssey[/b] expansion — required
[*][url=https://steamcommunity.com/workshop/filedetails/?id=2009463077][b]Harmony[/b][/url] — required
[*][b]Ideology[/b] — optional: enables slave handling, prisoner conversion, and the full styling dialog
[/list]

[h2]Notes[/h2]
[list]
[*]Safe to add to an existing save. Removing mid-save is not recommended (as with most content mods).
[*]Load order: after Harmony and the expansions (the usual sort handles it).
[*]Source on [url=https://github.com/ChibiBot/Odyssey_HoloAI]GitHub[/url].
[/list]
